  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>This spell functions as&nbsp;hold person, except it can target any living creature.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Hold Person</h2>\n<p>The target becomes paralyzed and freezes in place. It is aware and breathes normally but can&rsquo;t take any physical actions, even speech. A held creature can&rsquo;t cast spells. Each round on its turn, the target can spend a full action to attempt a new saving throw to end the effect. This does not provoke attacks of opportunity. A winged creature that is paralyzed can&rsquo;t flap its wings and falls. A swimmer can&rsquo;t swim and may drown.</p>",
